div.p:
If any Diviſor conſiſt only of one ſignifying Figure & Cyphers, you muſt Divide only by the ſignifyng Figure, & from the Quotient cut off as many Figures towards the right-Hand, as there are Cyphers in the Diviſor, obſerving, that if the ſignifying Figure be only an Unite, You have no uſe for the Rotula, or any other Inſtrument; but meerly to write down the Dividend below the Line in the Quotient; & then cut off from it conform to the Number of your Cyphers. Example firſt;



                                 Diviſor 1000.) 976583 Dividend.

976583 Quotient.

