13. In any Plain Triangle, as the Diameter is to the verſed Sine of the vertical Angle;


So is the ſquare of the ſum of the legs leſs by the ſquare of the difference of the legs

To the ſquare of the Baſe leſs by the ſquare of the difference of the legs
